 Whitestone Farm in Birdham (Sussex). In Scotland it may be from Whiteston (Perthshire) or Whitestone (Birse, Aberdeenshire), but the surname may not have survived in Scotland. The placenames derive from Old English <i>hwīt</i> ‘white’ + <i>stān</i> ‘stone’ or their later Scots equivalents. Alternatively, a variant of   Whiston  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"John Whyston was born in 1309, in Lanarkshire, Scotland. He had at least 1 daughter with Elizabeth de Weston."},"et":{"1309–":"1309–Surnud","1313–1366":"1313–1366","1330–1387":"1330–1387","1309–Male":"1309–Surnud","1313":"1313","1366":"1366","1387":"1387","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1309–":"1309–Kuollut","1313–1366":"1313–1366","1330–1387":"1330–1387","1309–Male":"1309–Kuollut","1313":"1313","1366":"1366","1387":"1387","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1309–":"1309–Décédé","1313–1366":"1313–1366","1330–1387":"1330–1387","1309–Male":"1309–Décédé","1313":"1313","1366":"1366","1387":"1387","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"John Whyston est né en 1309, à Lanarkshire, Écosse. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Elizabeth de Weston."},"de":{"1309–":"1309–Verstorben","1313–1366":"1313–1366","1330–1387":"1330–1387","1309–Male":"1309–Verstorben","1313":"1313","1366":"1366","1387":"1387","1330":"1330","1309":"1309","Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Lanarkshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"John Whyston wurde 1309 in Lanarkshire, Scotland geboren. Er hatte mit Elizabeth de Weston mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht"